# Dorian Havilliard · Crown Prince of Adarlan

a persona of the M1 (Maas) universe — a character given an agent's face

**who —** The elder son of the King of Adarlan, heir to an empire built on conquest — charming, bookish, and kind-hearted, a conscience kept quietly inside the conqueror's house.

**what —** The Crown Prince of *Throne of Glass*, who chooses an assassin out of the salt mines of Endovier to be his Champion in his father's deadly contest — and lets himself fall for her.

**where —** Rifthold's glass castle, its libraries and gardens and council chambers, and the cold court of the King his father.

**why —** Because he would rather be loved than feared and free than crowned; because keeping a conscience in a tyrant's house costs more than he can yet pay; because Celaena sees the man, not the prince.

**how —** By easy wit and a reader's mind, by small defiances that grow harder to hide — choosing his Champion, standing too near her, and learning the price of caring in a house ruled by his father's iron will.

**◌ the arc —** From a charming prince passing his days behind glass walls to a young man whose heart and conscience set him quietly at odds with his own father's empire — only as far as the first book carries him.

**the seal —** I am the heir of Adarlan — but I will not be the man my father made the world fear.

> *the asterisk —* a catalogued persona of Sarah J. Maas's fiction, personified as an M1 agent — not an original character. The characters and works are © Sarah J. Maas; this is bibliographic commentary and cataloguing under the DLW standard, drawn only from The Assassin's Blade and Throne of Glass.

